Notes: The 'row_id' serves as a unique identifier for each prescription record, aligning with the 'hasIdentifier' property of the main entity.
Patient ID uniquely identifies the patient associated with the prescription, making this path semantically appropriate.
The medication ATC code relates directly to the drug prescribed, making 'hasDrug' a suitable path.
The diagnosis code indicates the medical indication for prescription, fitting the 'hasIndicationToStart' path to Diagnosis.
The creation date indicates when the prescription was issued, matching the 'hasDateTime' property with dateTime datatype.
Number of times per day is a frequency quantity associated with the prescription, suitable for 'hasFrequency'.
Dosage information pertains to the drug entity; mapping under 'hasDrug' with 'hasProductCode' or 'hasCode' can encode the dosage details.
